<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{5}{y}={39}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3}{x}-{7}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{5}{y}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={39}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{39}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{\left(\frac{{{39}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}\right)}+-{7}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{3}}{{8}}\cdot{\left({39}\right)}-\frac{{3}}{{8}}{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{14.625}-{\left({1.875}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.875}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}={30}-{14.625}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.875}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}={15.375}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({1.875}+{\left(-{7}\right)}\right)}{y}={15.375}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5.125}{y}={15.375}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{15.375}}{{-{{5.125}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{5}{\left(-{3}\right)}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left({15}\right)}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={39}-{\left({15}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{24}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
